name: Ben Hunt
tweet: I understand people focusing on the AIG backstop as an egregious bailout of Goldman Sachs. And it was.  But banks don’t fail from insolvency. They fail from illiquidity.   AIG (asset support) was a nice-to-have for GS. TLGP (funding support) was the must-have.

name: Ben Hunt
tweet: Despite insolvency & illiquidity, Goldman Sachs paid its partners and employees $10 BILLION in comp and benefits in 2008. To fund itself, GS borrowed $29 BILLION in unsecured debt at 2% interest through loans co-signed by the US Treasury. To this day, GS denies it was bailed out.
